1. DEFINITIONS
- “Engine” refers to the Void Engine and all its source code, assets, documentation, and related materials.
- “Software using the Engine” means any application, game, or program developed using Void Engine as a dependency or framework.
- “Plugin or Extension” means a separate, add-on component that interacts with Void Engine without modifying its core source code.
- “Derivative Work” means any modification or fork of Void Engine’s source code.

